        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 4 at 3:16PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 316 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles northwest of Segundo, or 19 miles west of Trinidad, moving
east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Trinidad, Cokedale, Starkville, Boncarbo, Segundo, Gulnare and
Weston.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
